description: The French president has ruled out resigning or dissolving the Assemblée Nationale, the latter of which some in his camp see as inevitable. headline: From Meta AI to ChatGPT: The dangerous game of ever-increasing AI personalization
description: While publicly pledging to design safe tools, Meta and OpenAI continue to give users the ability to steer their chatbots away from relative neutrality. Is this paradox sustainable in the long term?

headline: Video: Why are young African women manufacturing Russian drones?
description: The Alabuga Special Economic Zone, in Tatarstan, Russia, has been producing drones since the start of the war in Ukraine. There, young African women have found themselves working on production lines, lured by a misleading vocational training program.

headline: Mohammed Hilles' first days in France after arriving from Gaza: 'I went to a baroque concert at the Philharmonie. It filled me with joy, sadness and nostalgia'
description: Hilles, 25, left Gaza to study music at Paris-Saclay University. After the initial relief of his arrival, he has grown increasingly worried about his family in the Palestinian enclave.

headline: Ultra-processed foods cause negative health effects within weeks, study finds
description: In a clinical trial similar to those used for testing medicines, scientists studied the health impacts of a diet filled with ultra-processed foods. Results show that numerous biological processes are affected.
